    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A small to medium-sized, long-living evergreen oak found mostly in cold semi-arid to temperate humid regions of the Mediterranean basin. It has small leathery and wooly leaves with an upper side of dark green, and a lower side covered in white hairs. The wood of the tree is dense and semiporous, and is often used as firewood. Its acorns have been used to feed livestock.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
